261
00:19:56.729 --> 00:19:59.756
Nicky. even if it does
exist. what about it?

262
00:19:59.774 --> 00:20:01.296
I own it.

263
00:20:08.116 --> 00:20:09.684
Yeah.

264
00:20:16.958 --> 00:20:21.021
The directions in the will had
the house in town on this road.

265
00:20:23.381 --> 00:20:26.280
There's no sign a
town was ever here.

266
00:20:28.761 --> 00:20:31.530
This baby is sailing. man.
You did a lot of work on it.

267
00:20:31.556 --> 00:20:34.454
How are we supposed to find a
house without a street address?

268
00:20:36.394 --> 00:20:37.916
Hey. babe. how you feeling?

269
00:20:39.272 --> 00:20:43.202
Can we please just find a
place that has a bathroom?

270
00:20:43.526 --> 00:20:47.304
I can't find a town or even a
bowling alley called River's End.

271
00:21:20.104 --> 00:21:22.126
Oh my god. that dog
has three legs.

272
00:21:22.148 --> 00:21:24.299
So?
So don't order any meat.

273
00:21:24.317 --> 00:21:27.253
That's quite a set of wheels.
Thank you.

274
00:21:27.278 --> 00:21:29.630
It was my granddad's.
Bathroom?

275
00:21:29.655 --> 00:21:31.678
Down the hall. past
the cigarette machine.

276
00:21:37.205 --> 00:21:39.524
Hey.

277
00:21:39.540 --> 00:21:42.101
River's End. this... this is it.

278
00:21:42.168 --> 00:21:44.900
Ryo. look.
Holy shit.

279
00:21:44.921 --> 00:21:48.240
Look! Look at this!

280
00:21:53.471 --> 00:21:55.744
This house. we're looking for it.

281
00:21:55.765 --> 00:21:58.618
Are you all those folks that
came through this morning?

282
00:21:58.643 --> 00:22:01.337
That van had a state
logo on it. Knoxie.

283
00:22:01.354 --> 00:22:02.876
This place?

284
00:22:02.897 --> 00:22:04.840
I own it.

285
00:22:04.857 --> 00:22:07.881
You own Wormwood?

286
00:22:07.902 --> 00:22:09.254
Wormwood?

287
00:22:11.155 --> 00:22:12.315
That's the name of the house?

288
00:22:12.365 --> 00:22:14.968
Yeah. after the flood
washed it away.

289
00:22:17.620 --> 00:22:21.941
You know. food for the worms?

290
00:22:21.958 --> 00:22:25.107
You've never heard of
the Blackwater flood?

291
00:22:25.127 --> 00:22:26.854
20-something years ago?

292
00:22:26.879 --> 00:22:28.356
It was the end. all right.

293
00:22:28.381 --> 00:22:31.030
There is no River's End.

294
00:22:31.092 --> 00:22:33.468
Washed away. all of it.

295
00:22:33.469 --> 00:22:37.373
Town doesn't exist anymore...
same as your house.

296
00:22:37.431 --> 00:22:39.659
Unless you like old wives' tales.

297
00:22:39.684 --> 00:22:42.037
Well. yeah. I might like them.

298
00:22:42.061 --> 00:22:44.664
Don't shovel that shit
to these kids. Lucky.

299
00:22:44.689 --> 00:22:48.419
There's one story that says
that house is still standing.

300
00:22:52.446 --> 00:22:58.302
Story says the flood hit that house
hard. but it didn't take it down.

301
00:22:58.327 --> 00:22:59.974
Couldn't take it down.

302
00:22:59.996 --> 00:23:03.270
Just washed it from
here all the way

303
00:23:03.374 --> 00:23:06.668
down to here somewhere.

304
00:23:06.669 --> 00:23:09.989
If you believe stories
for idiots and morons.

305
00:23:10.006 --> 00:23:12.655
You got some kind of deed?

306
00:23:12.675 --> 00:23:15.244
'Cause you're about
23 years too late.

307
00:23:25.730 --> 00:23:27.082
What?

308
00:23:39.869 --> 00:23:42.017
Nicky.

309
00:23:42.038 --> 00:23:45.975
That house isn't the only way to find
out about your father or anyone else.

310
00:23:46.000 --> 00:23:47.352
Hey.

311
00:23:49.545 --> 00:23:50.942
That's weird.

312
00:23:50.963 --> 00:23:54.033
Yeah. like "Texas Chainsaw" weird.

313
00:23:54.050 --> 00:23:54.571
Aughhh!

314
00:23:54.592 --> 00:23:55.363
Look out!

315
00:23:59.347 --> 00:24:00.073
Hey.

316
00:24:00.097 --> 00:24:00.914
You all right?

317
00:24:00.931 --> 00:24:01.431
Hey.

318
00:24:01.432 --> 00:24:02.658
Yeah.

319
00:24:05.019 --> 00:24:05.899
You guys all right?

320
00:24:05.936 --> 00:24:07.538
You came out of nowhere. man.

321
00:24:07.563 --> 00:24:10.253
Sorry.
You OK?

322
00:24:13.444 --> 00:24:14.966
You OK?

323
00:24:16.989 --> 00:24:18.306
That was close.
Is everybody all right?

324
00:24:18.324 --> 00:24:19.425
Yeah.

325
00:24:19.450 --> 00:24:20.893
I am so sorry.

326
00:24:20.910 --> 00:24:23.854
We haven't seen any other
cars out here all day.

327
00:24:23.871 --> 00:24:24.472
I'm Chris.

328
00:24:24.497 --> 00:24:25.564
I'm Sam.

329
00:24:25.581 --> 00:24:27.103
That's Lillith.

330
00:24:29.335 --> 00:24:30.812
Hello.

331
00:24:30.836 --> 00:24:31.528
That your van?

332
00:24:31.545 --> 00:24:34.740
Yeah. PLS.

333
00:24:34.757 --> 00:24:36.109
Public Land and Survey?

334
00:24:36.175 --> 00:24:37.948
We're out here mapping the
valley for the state.

335
00:24:38.010 --> 00:24:39.737
Yeah. what are you doing out here?

336
00:24:39.762 --> 00:24:44.162
Well. we were looking for a house. till we
found out that it got washed down a ridge.

337
00:24:44.183 --> 00:24:47.787
Wormwood? House that washed into
the valley during the flood?

338
00:24:47.853 --> 00:24:51.333
Yeah. You guys think you
know something about that?

339
00:24:52.650 --> 00:24:54.923
Yeah. if you believe
in urban myths.

340
00:25:01.409 --> 00:25:03.762
This is Wormwood. huh?

341
00:25:11.293 --> 00:25:14.526
Sam?
Yeah. boss?

342
00:25:14.547 --> 00:25:15.864
What she said.

343
00:25:15.881 --> 00:25:17.858
We should just keep one
foot in reality here.

344
00:25:17.925 --> 00:25:20.635
Any house. even if it survived
being ripped off its

345
00:25:20.636 --> 00:25:24.365
foundation. would break into
kindling. crashing through trees.

346
00:25:24.682 --> 00:25:26.034
Well. look. if there's any
part of it around here. like

347
00:25:26.058 --> 00:25:30.128
a... a floorboard or a roof shingle...
anything... I'd like to see it.

348
00:25:30.146 --> 00:25:32.795
Um. I'm telling you.
it's an urban myth.

349
00:25:35.443 --> 00:25:38.012
Get in your car. Follow me.

350
00:25:39.572 --> 00:25:40.719
Hey. wait. wait. wait.

351
00:25:40.740 --> 00:25:42.057
Aagghh!

352
00:25:42.074 --> 00:25:43.050
Mmph!

353
00:25:45.995 --> 00:25:46.971
Nicky. Nicky.

354
00:25:46.996 --> 00:25:49.273
Is he OK?
Yes. he's OK. He's OK.

355
00:25:49.320 --> 00:25:53.106
He just... he gets dizzy spells
when he thinks too fast. Nick?

356
00:25:53.127 --> 00:25:54.604
Look at me.

357
00:25:54.670 --> 00:25:57.691
How about you get back in
the car and sit down. OK?

358
00:25:59.008 --> 00:26:00.951
What do you mean?

359
00:26:00.968 --> 00:26:04.789
It's a long shot. but we
mapped something a few days

360
00:26:04.805 --> 00:26:07.751
ago that I think you need to see.

361
00:26:36.045 --> 00:26:39.274
This is the old highway where
the flood took it out.

362
00:26:39.298 --> 00:26:41.821
See this path through the forest?

363
00:26:41.842 --> 00:26:43.785
Something big definitely
came through here.

364
00:26:43.803 --> 00:26:46.701
Yeah. it's called a flood.
No.

365
00:26:46.764 --> 00:26:50.093
Look at the sway of these trees.
It's way above the flood line.

366
00:26:50.518 --> 00:26:53.295
Come on. Chris. there's ravines
like this throughout the county.

367
00:26:53.312 --> 00:26:56.670
Thanks. Sam. But on this team.
I'm the arboriculturalist.

368
00:26:56.690 --> 00:26:58.167
God. not that word again.

369
00:26:58.192 --> 00:26:59.776
He likes to say that 'cause
he thinks it sounds dirty.

370
00:26:59.777 --> 00:27:03.452
No. wait. so you're
a tree guy. right?

371
00:27:04.406 --> 00:27:05.553
Nicky. Nicky.

372
00:27:05.616 --> 00:27:07.093
Baby. come back up
here with me. OK?

373
00:27:07.159 --> 00:27:09.228
Yeah. come on.
Nick. why don't you. huh?

374
00:27:09.745 --> 00:27:11.264
Baby. now. Please?

375
00:27:11.330 --> 00:27:12.852
What?

376
00:27:26.011 --> 00:27:28.284
At least one house
came through here.

377
00:27:31.559 --> 00:27:35.334
It's. uh. it's a long shot.

378
00:27:35.354 --> 00:27:38.207
But we could all go for
a quick little hike.

379
00:27:41.360 --> 00:27:44.464
He said it was a long shot. Nicky.

380
00:27:44.488 --> 00:27:47.492
A shot's still a shot. Evie.

381
00:27:48.117 --> 00:27:49.639
Come on.

382
00:27:49.660 --> 00:27:52.413
You gonna be OK here if I...
if I take a quick look?

383
00:27:52.538 --> 00:27:54.356
I'm not hiking. if that's
what you mean.

384
00:27:54.415 --> 00:27:56.688
It's only gonna be a few minutes.
Ryo. can you stay here with her?

385
00:27:56.750 --> 00:27:57.890
Please? All right?

386
00:27:57.911 --> 00:27:59.433
Come on. Sam.
I know you want to come.

387
00:27:59.454 --> 00:28:00.931
Yeah. I'm only going to see
your face when all you find is

388
00:28:01.755 --> 00:28:03.903
poison ivy and a couple
of humping beavers.

389
00:28:06.427 --> 00:28:07.824
Lil?

390
00:28:07.845 --> 00:28:09.947
Ooh. thanks. but uh.
I think I'll stay with Eve.

391
00:28:09.972 --> 00:28:11.324
That's a great idea.

392
00:28:15.978 --> 00:28:20.048
I'm leaving in the van if you guys
aren't back here in 10 minutes.

393
00:28:20.065 --> 00:28:21.917
And I'm taking Eve with me.

394
00:28:21.942 --> 00:28:22.884
Eve.

395
00:28:22.943 --> 00:28:24.386
I love you.

396
00:28:27.573 --> 00:28:30.927
See how the slip
plane moves across?

397
00:28:30.951 --> 00:28:33.429
This isn't just from the water.

398
00:28:33.454 --> 00:28:34.726
It is...

399
00:28:34.747 --> 00:28:37.020
So I just follow where
the trees are clear?

400
00:28:37.041 --> 00:28:38.393
Yeah. exactly.

401
00:28:43.005 --> 00:28:45.115
Nick!
Nicky. slow down!

402
00:28:48.010 --> 00:28:49.327
Nicky!

403
00:28:52.973 --> 00:28:53.949
Nicky!

404
00:28:53.974 --> 00:28:55.291
Come on!

405
00:28:58.687 --> 00:29:02.417
We're gonna get lost out here.

406
00:29:02.441 --> 00:29:05.044
You gonna be OK?

407
00:29:05.069 --> 00:29:06.796
We gotta get back.

408
00:29:12.451 --> 00:29:13.177
Little window.

409
00:29:13.243 --> 00:29:14.686
Right. Nicky?

410
00:29:17.915 --> 00:29:19.858
Little round window at the top?

411
00:30:00.833 --> 00:30:02.731
What the hell are we looking at?

412
00:30:16.181 --> 00:30:18.784
This is wrong.
Come on. this is wrong.

413
00:30:18.809 --> 00:30:22.333
It should have been pulverized.
This can't be the same house.

414
00:30:22.354 --> 00:30:23.876
Oh. yeah?

415
00:30:23.897 --> 00:30:25.249
Then what is it?

416
00:30:49.173 --> 00:30:50.866
That's not even from this house.

417
00:30:50.924 --> 00:30:54.427
You gonna tell me this whole place
just crashed here. perfectly level?

418
00:30:54.428 --> 00:30:58.658
Well. maybe someone leveled it.

419
00:30:58.682 --> 00:31:01.331
I think a lot of big stuff must
have washed through here.

420
00:31:04.104 --> 00:31:09.707
And when the house did.
I think that's the tree that

421
00:31:10.027 --> 00:31:11.674
finally stopped it.

422
00:31:11.695 --> 00:31:14.344
I just got this really
weird feeling. Ryan.

423
00:31:18.494 --> 00:31:21.438
I drew this.

424
00:31:21.455 --> 00:31:23.649
I dreamed this.

425
00:31:23.665 --> 00:31:27.065
And now I'm standing in
front of it. like I'm

426
00:31:27.086 --> 00:31:29.587
the reason it's here.

427
00:31:29.588 --> 00:31:31.816
Like it's holding on. just for me.

428
00:31:31.840 --> 00:31:33.408
Stop right there.

429
00:31:44.228 --> 00:31:47.753
Now turn around and walk away.

430
00:31:50.692 --> 00:31:52.465
Look. don't get the wrong idea.

431
00:31:52.486 --> 00:31:55.430
We're. uh. Public Land and Survey.

432
00:32:12.464 --> 00:32:13.690
I'm Sam.

433
00:32:13.757 --> 00:32:17.236
I know who you are. Sammael.

434
00:32:17.261 --> 00:32:19.989
Heh.

435
00:32:20.013 --> 00:32:21.365
It... it's Sam.

436
00:32:37.781 --> 00:32:40.100
You with the state. too?

437
00:32:40.117 --> 00:32:42.724
No.
I'm with...

438
00:32:42.744 --> 00:32:46.598
Look. if we ended up somewhere we
shouldn't be. we apologize. Mister...?

439
00:32:46.665 --> 00:32:49.860
My name's Seth.

440
00:32:49.877 --> 00:32:52.571
That's all you need to know.

441
00:32:52.588 --> 00:32:54.907
And let me tell you
something else. Sammael.

442
00:32:54.923 --> 00:32:56.320
It's Sam.

443
00:32:56.341 --> 00:32:57.738
I don't know what you think
you're doing here. or what

444
00:32:57.759 --> 00:33:00.703
claim you think you
have to this house...

445
00:33:00.721 --> 00:33:02.289
We're just mapping the valley.

446
00:33:02.306 --> 00:33:05.367
But if this is about eminent domain
or any of that state bullshit...

447
00:33:05.392 --> 00:33:06.493
it's a geodesic survey.

448
00:33:06.518 --> 00:33:09.061
We don't care about this house.
Make no mistake.

449
00:33:09.062 --> 00:33:14.995
I've been swinging a hammer in
it since before you were born.

450
00:33:15.319 --> 00:33:17.137
I've been working
this place forever.

451
00:33:20.699 --> 00:33:23.518
And I'm here to stay.

452
00:33:23.577 --> 00:33:25.600
We don't want any trouble.

453
00:33:25.621 --> 00:33:28.941
Then you best be on your way.

454
00:33:28.957 --> 00:33:30.229
I th...

455
00:33:30.250 --> 00:33:31.818
I think you're probably right.

456
00:33:40.010 --> 00:33:40.861
Wait.

457
00:33:40.886 --> 00:33:42.238
The people that lived here.

458
00:33:44.598 --> 00:33:46.120
Do you know anything about them?

459
00:33:46.141 --> 00:33:48.710
No. Nicky.

460
00:33:48.769 --> 00:33:51.372
The man who used to
live here 20 years ago.

461
00:33:51.396 --> 00:33:52.918
What about him?

462
00:33:55.734 --> 00:33:57.211
I just want to know his name.

463
00:34:00.405 --> 00:34:02.473
No.

464
00:34:02.491 --> 00:34:03.968
No you don't.

465
00:34:07.913 --> 00:34:09.560
Look. this house is
in my mother's will.

466
00:34:09.581 --> 00:34:11.183
These people might be my family.

467
00:34:14.336 --> 00:34:16.609
I have the deed.

468
00:34:16.630 --> 00:34:17.947
I don't care what you have.

469
00:34:17.965 --> 00:34:19.942
What you came looking
for isn't here.

470
00:34:20.008 --> 00:34:22.987
You do not know what
I came looking for.

471
00:34:39.361 --> 00:34:42.305
Just you.

472
00:34:42.364 --> 00:34:45.308
Not your buddy.

473
00:34:45.325 --> 00:34:47.018
And no one from the state.

474
00:34:51.832 --> 00:34:55.933
You want to see this house
you think is yours?

475
00:34:56.253 --> 00:34:59.482
Come on.

476
00:34:59.506 --> 00:35:01.483
What. do you think
he's a fucking realtor?

477
00:35:01.508 --> 00:35:02.985
Look at him.

478
00:35:05.053 --> 00:35:06.029
Nick!

479
00:35:06.054 --> 00:35:08.248
Your old man's not in there!

480
00:35:29.661 --> 00:35:31.763
I drew this house
when I was a kid.

481
00:35:35.125 --> 00:35:39.196
God. it had all of this in it.

482
00:35:39.212 --> 00:35:41.781
Every room. upstairs.

483
00:35:46.303 --> 00:35:47.279
Downstairs.

484
00:35:52.017 --> 00:35:53.369
What is that?

485
00:35:59.232 --> 00:36:02.051
What's in the walls?

486
00:36:03.028 --> 00:36:04.550
Rats?

487
00:36:12.037 --> 00:36:13.354
That's abhorrent.

488
00:36:26.843 --> 00:36:30.856
That's the tree at the side of the house.
They lynched people from that tree.

489
00:36:34.226 --> 00:36:36.374
You ever see a hanging tree. boy?

490
00:36:39.564 --> 00:36:43.256
Who lives here?
Look around.

491
00:36:43.276 --> 00:36:44.969
Nobody lives here.

492
00:36:44.986 --> 00:36:47.054
Who used to live here?

493
00:36:52.411 --> 00:36:54.184
What the hell is that?

494
00:36:56.415 --> 00:36:57.858
What's that in the chimney?

495
00:36:57.874 --> 00:37:01.399
The deed you have to this house is

496
00:37:01.420 --> 00:37:05.756
worthless. just like the house.

497
00:37:05.757 --> 00:37:11.988
Look. I just want to know if
people from my family lived here.

498
00:37:12.013 --> 00:37:13.365
Nick!

499
00:37:18.895 --> 00:37:19.871
Hey.

500
00:37:19.896 --> 00:37:20.838
Time's up.

501
00:37:20.856 --> 00:37:21.752
Let's go. buddy.

502
00:37:21.773 --> 00:37:23.625
Let's get back to the car. OK?

503
00:37:23.650 --> 00:37:25.969
Sam and Chris say they have help.

504
00:37:26.027 --> 00:37:28.129
How do you like your house. Nick?

505
00:37:30.532 --> 00:37:32.885
You seen enough?

506
00:37:32.951 --> 00:37:36.745
Are you not understanding
something. Nick?

507
00:37:36.746 --> 00:37:42.690
When the flood came and wiped out this
town. people blamed... this house!

508
00:37:46.423 --> 00:37:47.991
Did you know that?

509
00:37:50.010 --> 00:37:52.704
Survivors called it the Second
Flood of Noah because they

510
00:37:52.721 --> 00:38:01.157
thought it came from God to
wash away this house and all

511
00:38:01.480 --> 00:38:03.924
the horrors that came with it.

512
00:38:03.940 --> 00:38:08.883
This place was ripped from the
earth and slammed into that tree.

513
00:38:08.904 --> 00:38:11.655
Instead of a pile of broken
sticks. it's all still here.

514
00:38:11.656 --> 00:38:14.100
Chairs. tables. chandeliers...

515
00:38:14.117 --> 00:38:15.935
they shouldn't be here. Nick.

516
00:38:15.952 --> 00:38:17.645
I thought you said that was you.

517
00:38:17.662 --> 00:38:21.437
You said you'd been swinging
a hammer in here for years.

518
00:38:21.458 --> 00:38:23.686
I have.

519
00:38:23.710 --> 00:38:27.485
I've been trying to tear it down.

520
00:38:27.506 --> 00:38:29.108
Nick. let's go!

521
00:38:45.357 --> 00:38:52.962
You tell you friend
